---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { SITE_NAME, SITE_URL } from '../lib/constants';

const title = 'Terms of Service — Usage Terms, Conditions & Policy';
const description = `${SITE_NAME} terms of service. Understand the terms and conditions governing your use of our free paycheck calculators, tax tools, and financial resources.`;
---

<Layout title={title} description={description} noIndex={true}>
  <section class="px-4 py-16 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="prose prose-slate dark:prose-invert mx-auto max-w-3xl">
      <h1>Terms of Service</h1>
      <p><strong>Last updated:</strong> June 2026</p>

      <h2>1. Acceptance of Terms</h2>
      <p>
        By accessing and using {SITE_NAME} ({SITE_URL}), you agree to be bound by these Terms of Service.
        If you do not agree with any part of these terms, please do not use our website. These terms apply
        to all users, including browsers, visitors, and contributors.
      </p>

      <h2>2. Description of Service</h2>
      <p>
        {SITE_NAME} is an independent information platform providing free online calculators and
        informational content related to paycheck calculations, federal and state income tax estimates,
        FICA (Social Security and Medicare) deductions, retirement planning, and other personal finance
        topics for the United States. All tools are provided "as is" for informational and educational
        purposes only.
      </p>

      <h2>3. Not Professional Advice</h2>
      <p>
        <strong>The calculations, results, and content provided by {SITE_NAME} do not constitute tax
        advice, financial advice, legal advice, or any other professional advice.</strong> Our calculators
        provide estimates based on general tax rules published by the IRS and state tax authorities, and
        may not account for your specific situation, including deductions, credits, filing status
        adjustments, and other individual circumstances. Always consult a qualified CPA, tax professional,
        financial advisor, or attorney for advice specific to your circumstances.
      </p>

      <h2>4. Privacy and Data Protection</h2>
      <p>
        All calculations are performed entirely in your browser using client-side JavaScript. No salary,
        tax, or financial data is transmitted to our servers. We use Plausible Analytics, a privacy-friendly
        service that uses no cookies, stores no personal data, and is fully compliant with GDPR and CCPA.
        URL parameters exist only in your browser and are not stored server-side. See our full
        <a href="/privacy-policy/">Privacy Policy</a> for details.
      </p>

      <h2>5. Cookies and Local Storage</h2>
      <p>
        This website uses no tracking cookies. No advertising, profiling, or third-party cookies are placed.
        User preferences (such as dark/light mode) are stored in the browser's localStorage, which is not a
        cookie and is never transmitted to our servers. Since no tracking cookies are used, a cookie consent
        banner is not legally required.
      </p>

      <h2>6. Accuracy</h2>
      <p>
        While we strive for accuracy and regularly update our tax data and formulas based on IRS publications
        and state tax authority data, we cannot guarantee that calculations will be error-free or reflect the
        most current tax laws. Tax laws change frequently at both federal and state levels, and individual
        circumstances vary. You are responsible for verifying any calculations before making financial
        decisions. We recommend using the official IRS withholding calculator for verification.
      </p>

      <h2>7. Use of Service</h2>
      <p>You agree to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Use the service only for lawful purposes</li>
        <li>Not attempt to reverse-engineer, scrape, or systematically access the service without permission</li>
        <li>Not misrepresent calculator results as professional advice</li>
        <li>Not use the service in any way that could damage or impair it</li>
        <li>Not use automated systems to extract data from the website without express permission</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>8. Intellectual Property</h2>
      <p>
        All content, design, code, calculation algorithms, and calculators on {SITE_NAME} are the property
        of Mottalib Radif and are protected by copyright and other intellectual property laws. You may use
        the calculators for personal, non-commercial use but may not reproduce, distribute, or create
        derivative works without prior written permission. Brief quotations for informational purposes are
        permitted provided the source is credited.
      </p>

      <h2>9. GDPR Rights (EU Users)</h2>
      <p>
        Under the GDPR, EU users have the right to access, rectify, erase, restrict processing, data
        portability, object to processing, and withdraw consent at any time. Since no personal data is
        collected through our calculators, these rights are satisfied by default. You have the right to
        lodge a complaint with your national data protection authority. For enquiries, contact us at
        contact@truetakehomepay.com.
      </p>

      <h2>10. CCPA Rights (California Residents)</h2>
      <p>
        Under the CCPA, California residents have the right to know what personal information is collected,
        request deletion, opt out of the sale of personal information, and not be discriminated against.
        Since we do not collect personal information through our calculators and do not sell personal data,
        these rights are exercised by default.
      </p>

      <h2>11. Limitation of Liability</h2>
      <p>
        {SITE_NAME} shall not be liable for any damages arising from the use or inability to use our
        service, including but not limited to direct, indirect, incidental, punitive, or consequential
        damages. This includes any losses resulting from reliance on calculator results. The website is
        provided on an "as is" and "as available" basis without warranties of any kind, express or implied,
        including but not limited to implied warranties of merchantability, fitness for a particular purpose,
        and non-infringement.
      </p>
      <p>
        The publisher is not responsible for data loss, service interruptions, or damages to user equipment
        resulting from the use of the website.
      </p>

      <h2>12. External Links</h2>
      <p>
        This website may contain links to external websites, including IRS.gov, state tax authority websites,
        and other reference sources. The publisher has no control over the content of these sites and
        disclaims all responsibility for their content, privacy practices, or availability.
      </p>

      <h2>13. Governing Law</h2>
      <p>
        These terms are governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of the United States. Any
        disputes arising from the use of this website shall be subject to the exclusive jurisdiction of
        the courts of the United States. The potential invalidity of any clause shall not affect the
        remaining provisions.
      </p>

      <h2>14. Changes and Contact</h2>
      <p>
        We reserve the right to modify these terms at any time. Continued use of the service after changes
        constitutes acceptance of the revised terms. For questions, contact us at:<br />
        Email: <a href="mailto:contact@truetakehomepay.com">contact@truetakehomepay.com</a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
